I'd hate to sound over the top, but this place is like an oasis. Surrounded by mediocrity, the food here is on another level when compared to everything else being offered in the neighborhood. There were even quite a few times where I chose to call from My Pizza instead of bigger names like Domino's and Papa Johns. Aside from the great tasting food, I really have no complaints. The place is usually clean and I've never had a problem with the staff myself. The biggest complaint I have is delivery is inconsistent, and so are the toppings if you aren't descriptive. Ordering delivery is like gambling, you either get your order or you don't and you're stuck waiting in the cold. I recall once forgetting to be descriptive with my topics, and I'll be honest, they were in a rush to get my order finished and move on. If you're anywhere near this place and you're itching for something quick to eat, you really can't go wrong here. Alternatively if you're looking for cheap delivery and you don't want to sacrifice quality for price, don't be afraid to give them a call.
